# FvwmButtons - PagerPanel
#
# FvwmButtons is a powerful module that can be used to build custom
# panels and docks. This config uses FvwmButtons to build the PagerPanel.
# The panel contains buttons to switch desks, FvwmPager, a system tray,
# FvwmIconMan (list of running windows), and a clock.
#
# Note - To use the system tray you must have "stalonetray" installed.
DestroyModuleConfig PagerPanel:*
*PagerPanel: Geometry 156x220-4+4
*PagerPanel: Colorset 22
*PagerPanel: Rows 32
*PagerPanel: Columns 120
*PagerPanel: Frame 1
*PagerPanel: Font "xft:Roboto:Bold:size=9:antialias=True"
*PagerPanel: (120x6, Swallow DateTime 'Module FvwmScript $[FVWM_USERDIR]/scripts/FvwmScript-Clock', Frame 0)
*PagerPanel: (120x10, Swallow FvwmPager 'Module FvwmPager *', Frame 0)
*PagerPanel: (30x3, Id desk0, Title "1", Action (Mouse 1) GotoDesk 0 0, Colorset 11, ActiveColorset 12, Frame 0)
*PagerPanel: (30x3, Id desk1, Title "2", Action (Mouse 1) GotoDesk 0 1, ActiveColorset 12, Frame 0)
*PagerPanel: (30x3, Id desk2, Title "3", Action (Mouse 1) GotoDesk 0 2, ActiveColorset 12, Frame 0)
*PagerPanel: (30x3, Id desk3, Title "4", Action (Mouse 1) GotoDesk 0 3, ActiveColorset 12, Frame 0)
*PagerPanel: (120x4, Swallow(NoClose,UseOld) stalonetray 'Exec exec stalonetray --config "/home/doug/.stalonetrayrc"', Frame 0)
# Test (x stalonetray) *PagerPanel: (120x3, Swallow(NoClose,UseOld) stalonetray 'Exec exec stalonetray --config "/home/doug/.stalonetrayrc"', Frame 0)

